Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Human BioScience is a leading multinational enterprise specialized in research & development as well as   the manufacturing of medicine for critical care therapies. HB Human Bioscience aims at the betterment of the health and well-being of people, through the implementation of state-of-the-art technology and cutting edge methods to the production of their medicine. Their products are certified by the most important pharmaceutical regulatory authorities in the world; namely, WHO, USFDA, MHRA,UK, EMEA, ORGANIZACION PANAMERICANA DE LA SALUD, and INVIMA. HB Human BioScience imports the best medicine products from the most recognized laboratories around the world. HB Human BioScience also develops molecules to create its own medicines and introduce them into de pharmaceutical industry. HB Human BioSience specializes also in “Orphan Drugs” which are pharmaceutical agents that have been developed specifically to treat rare medical conditions, referred to as an” orphan diseases”.  Due to their low returns or high costs many “Orphan drugs” are not always available or sufficient in many countries.  Orphan Diseases are rare diseases with an average prevalence of less than 5 cases per 10,000 inhabitants. These are usually genetic diseases and/or life threatening conditions. Today certain drugs exist for those treatments however due to the rarity of the diseases it is usually impractical to procure licenses to import however Human Bioscience has implemented an infrastructure to deliver these medicines to thousands of patients worldwide who are suffering from these conditions. Other fields in which HB Human Bioscience stands out are in the development of Active Principles, Bioequivalences and New Medicines. Towards this end HB Human Bioscience works closely with a great team of prestigious scientists who apply their knowledge and technology to produce better and safer medicines to heal or prolong the life of thousands of patients.

Full Description: ReGen Biologics, Inc. designs, develops, manufactures, and markets medical devices for the repair and generation of soft tissue in humans, primarily for orthopedic applications. The company’s proprietary collagen matrix technology includes applications in orthopedics, general surgery, spine, cardiovascular, and drug delivery. Its products include Menaflex collagen meniscus implant device, for use in surgical procedures for the reinforcement and repair of soft tissue injuries of the medial meniscus; and SharpShooter Tissue Repair System, an instrument that allows surgeons to place needles in hard-to-reach locations of the meniscus. The company sells its products in the United States, the European Union, the Republic of South Africa, Canada, Australia, Chile, and Japan. ReGen Biologics, Inc. was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Hackensack, New Jersey. On April 8, 2011, ReGen Biologics, Inc. filed a voluntary petition for reorganization under Chapter 11 in the U.S. Bankruptcy Court for the District of Delaware. Description: DMARC is a technical specification created by a group of organizations that want to help reduce the potential for email-based abuse.

Full Description: DMARC is a technical specification created by a group of organizations that want to help reduce the potential for email-based abuse by solving a couple of long-standing operational, deployment, and reporting issues related to email authentication protocols. DMARC standardizes how email receivers perform email authentication using the SPF and DKIM mechanisms. It enables senders to experience consistent authentication results for their messages at AOL, Gmail, Hotmail, Yahoo!, and other email receivers. DMARC’s mission is to promote the use of DMARC and related email authentication technologies to reduce fraudulent emails. It pursues its goal primarily through education delivered as a combination of articles, tutorials, conference presentations, and webinars. DMARC was founded in 2010.
